Model Comparison: Main Models

pacman::p_load(MetaStan, cmdstanr, dplyr, tidyr, rio, here, data.table,
               posterior, ggdist, ggplot2, bayesplot)

# Set Stan options
options(mc.cores = parallel::detectCores())

Data

dat = data.frame(
  Study = c("Gonik (2016)", "Nossaman (2017)", "LaSala (2020)", "Zhang (2020)", 
            "Bassa (2021)", "Witt (2021)", "Zubaidaiah (2021)", "Bode (2022)", 
            "Sharma (2022)"),
  Experimental_Events = c(0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 2),
  Experimental_Total = c(12, 168, 20, 34, 13, 500, 30, 100, 100),
  Control_Events = c(0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 3),
  Control_Total = c(12, 224, 80, 30, 51, 502, 30, 101, 98)
)

setnames(dat, old=c("Experimental_Events","Control_Events"), new=c("r2", "r1"))
setnames(dat, old=c("Experimental_Total","Control_Total"), new=c("n2", "n1"))

J <- nrow(dat)  # Number of studies (84)
y <- as.matrix(dat[, c("r1", "r2")])  # Events: control (r1), treatment (r2)
sample <- as.matrix(dat[, c("n1", "n2")])  # Sample sizes: control (n1), treatment (n2)
zero <- c(0, 0)  # Zero vector for random effects mean

# Create the Stan data list
stan_data <- list(
  J = J,
  zero = zero,
  y = y,
  sample = sample
)

Models

zibglmm1_prior <- cmdstan_model(here("models/stan/zibglmm_prior_model1.stan"))
zibglmm2_prior <- cmdstan_model(here("models/stan/zibglmm_prior_model2.stan"))

zibglmm1 <- cmdstan_model(here("models/stan/zibglmm_model1.stan"))
zibglmm2 <- cmdstan_model(here("models/stan/zibglmm_model2.stan"))

Full

Model 1

csv_files <- list.files(here("models/storage"),
                        pattern = "^zibglmm_model1.*\\.csv$",
                        full.names = TRUE)

if (length(csv_files) > 0 && all(file.exists(csv_files))) {
  # Load the fit from CSV files
  fit1 <- cmdstanr::as_cmdstan_fit(csv_files)
  
} else {
  # Fit the model if no CSV files are found
  fit1 <- zibglmm1$sample(
    data = stan_data,
    chains = 4,
    parallel_chains = 4,
    iter_warmup = 2000,
    iter_sampling = 2000,
    adapt_delta = 0.99,  
    max_treedepth = 15,  
    seed = 123,
    refresh = 0
)
  
  # Save CSV files to persistent directory
  fit1$save_output_files(dir = "models/storage")
}

Parameters

Mu Control

data.frame(Posterior = parameters_draws1$`mu[1]`,
           # Normal(0, 2^2)
           Prior = parameters_draws1_prior$`mu[1]`) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = plogis(value), fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  #geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.005, fill = "gray70", color = "black") +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 0.15)) + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Model 1: mu prior Normal(0, 2^2)")
data.frame(Posterior = parameters_draws2$`mu[1]`,
           # Normal(0, 10^2)
           Prior = parameters_draws2_prior$`mu[1]`) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = plogis(value), fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  #geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.005, fill = "gray70", color = "black") +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 0.15)) + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Model 2: mu prior Normal(0, 10^2)")
data.frame(`Model 1` = parameters_draws1$`mu[1]`,
           `Model 2` = parameters_draws2$`mu[1]`) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = plogis(value), fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  #geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.005, fill = "gray70", color = "black") +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 0.15)) + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Posteriors: Model 1 vs. Model 2")

Estimands

# Extract posterior draws
estimands_draws1 <- fit1$draws(variables = c("p_control", "p_treatment",
                                           "RR", "OR", "RD"),
                             format = "df")

estimands_draws2 <- fit2$draws(variables = c("p_control", "p_treatment",
                                           "RR", "OR", "RD"),
                             format = "df")
tibble(`Control: Mod1` = estimands_draws1$p_control,
       `Control: Mod2` = estimands_draws2$p_control,
       `Treatment: Mod1` = estimands_draws1$p_treatment,
       `Treatment: Mod2` = estimands_draws2$p_treatment
       ) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = value, fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.3) +
  #geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = 2) +
  #scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 6, 1)) +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 0.2)) + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Posteriors: Risk")
tibble(`Posterior: Mod1` = estimands_draws1$RR,
       `Posterior: Mod2` = estimands_draws2$RR) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = value, fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = 2) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 6, 1)) +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 6)) + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Risk Ratio")
tibble(`Posterior: Mod1` = estimands_draws1$OR,
       `Posterior: Mod2` = estimands_draws2$OR) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = value, fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = 2) +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(0, 6)) + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 6, 1)) +
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Odds Ratio")
tibble(`Posterior: Mod1` = estimands_draws1$RD,
       `Posterior: Mod2` = estimands_draws2$RD) |> 
  pivot_longer(everything()) |> 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = value, fill = name) +
  stat_slab(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = 2) +
  coord_cartesian(x = c(-0.1, 0.1)) + 
 # scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 6, 1)) +
  theme_ggdist() +
  labs(title = "Risk Difference")
